President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Mark Green for a key administration post as a member of the Board of Directors of the Millennium Challenge Corporation. Green is currently the Managing Director of the Malaria No More Policy Center and has previously served as the U.S. Ambassador to the United Republic of Tanzania. He has also served four terms in the U.S. House of Representatives and has been involved in various legislative initiatives related to international relations and public health. Green holds a J.D. from the University of Wisconsin School of Law and a B.A. from the University of Wisconsin - Eau Claire.